name: BADGE | BUTTON | PIN By Gavin Lucas
description:
Badges, buttons and pins have been around for more than a century. 

Today they're everywhere: on lapels and bags all over the world and in the sketchbooks and on the screens of some of the hottest graphic designers, artists and illustrators. A badge can be a cheap and easy way to display political or cultural affiliations or it can simply be a fashion accessory. Cheap to produce and easy to make at home, the humble badge is the new T-shirt. A guide to the best and most beautiful badges being produced right now - be they graphic, textual or plain illustrative - this book explores the rich variety of uses of the badge since the year 2000, whether it be promotion, revenue-raising or simply decorative. 

The book will appeal to graphic designers, illustrators, fashion designers, artists, music lovers and badge enthusiasts of all ages.

500 illustrations
128 pages
200 x 200 mm

name: GUERILLA ART by Sebastian Peiter
description:
International street artists are currently conquering the art market, with auction houses, collectors and galleries demanding top prices for their work.

This book and DVD package features interviews with key artists including Banksy, Futura, Ramm:ell:zee, Os Gemeos, Invader, Barnstormers, WK Interact, Zevs, Blek le Rat, Andre, Noki and Eine. Graffiti-inspired street art pioneers Futura, Ramm:ell:zee and Blek le Rat discuss their own work, how street art was born out of the days of subway train graffiti, spraypainting and tagging, and how the new movement of street artists are doing things differently. Filmed in New York, London, Paris, Sao Paulo and Tokyo, the accompanying documentary shows the artists at work: Zevs practising his 'Visual Kidnappings' of advertising billboards, Blek le Rat sticking up outsized stencils, Os Gemeos painting their lyrical, folklore-inspired murals; and Invader putting up his unique mosaic wall tile images.

Hardback with DVD
200 illustrations
112 pages
230 x 190 mm

name: PANDAS ROCK by Pure Evil
description: Awesome Screen Print from Pure Evil, this is one of his first prints. Signed and hand numbered by Pure Evil, 700 x 500mm. Edition of 750 Frame not included

name: BANKSY STERLING NOTES Original by Tevés
description: We've been having a clear out and we are getting rid of some Gems that have been on the office wall, This original Sterling Notes printed onto discoloured recycled paper, 80gsm to look like Monopoly money. This beauty caused a right stir back in 2009 and was released as part of the 'Real Banksy' exhibition. 297mm x 210mm Signed and numbered edition of 10, this is number 10 Each note has a watermark style Kate Moss and Grannies where the Queen should be, please note this is not screen printed. Frame not included

name: KATE MOSS By Banksy 12" Artwork Sleeve
description:
Most of us will never be able to own an original Banksy, the next best thing are the limited edition 12" record sleeves that showcased Banksys artwork, mostly by Dirty Funker.

Original 12" double sided cover showcasing Banksy Kate Moss from 2009

name: BIG SMOKE by Neue
description:
To celebrate Black Friday Neue designed this re-work of the much replicated " I ❤ NY " with a Cockney twist. If you didn't manage to get your hands on one in our Black Friday Special offer there are still some left at the original price. 

Get your hands on this limited run of 100 prints in the 210mm X 210mm format on Conqueror off white 150GSM

Signed and numbered by the artist.

Frame not included

name: HANDGUN ORIGINAL by Scott King
description: Hand sketched and drawn with pencil, onto natural white paper and mounted on to card. 210x220mm Signed and hand numbered by Scott this is a one off original.

name: Dead Colour by ©opyKat
description: ONE of ONE, painted and framed piece. Size 540 x 400mm inc. frame An original water colour and stencil, one off piece created by ©opyKat. She believes the traditional art is dead and street art is here in a big way! Whether water colour is dead or not we love this girls stuff. Another strong statement from ©opyKat Framed water colour and stencil one off

name: AND by ©opyKat
description: Hand painted in a two tone black onto deep mounted canvas. AND has been hand painted onto the canvas by ©opyKat and she has then sprayed over the top giving the awesome subtle feel whilst also giving a raised effect. You almost think it's just a black square until the light reflects off it. 240mm x 300mm Signed and numbered edition of 3 This is number 1, please excuse our photography as the big boy broke and this has been shot on the tea boy's iPhone.

name: Invader by ©opyKat
description: At her best here with the 2012 Invader. An exquisite vintage oil painting by K.Bowman which has been re-mastered by ©opyKat, A modern day spin on the classic "Invader". A truly unique and individual piece finished with spray paint and acrylic mounted in a vintage Gold wooden frame Signed and hand numbered by the artist, one of one. This original comes framed. Size including frame 740mm wide by 635mm high

name: WALK AWAY ORIGINALS by Scott King
description: Scott King is back with a subtle dig at the financial crisis sweeping the UK. These lovely little originals sprayed onto cardboard would look awesome framed. 210 x 295mm in size Each is a signed and hand numbered Artist Proof by Scott, Limited Edition of only 1 in each colour way.

name: STORMPOOPER ORIGINAL GOLD PAINTED BOARD by Tevés
description: Hand painted onto wood board using spray paints. Size 420 x 594mm This beauty was done by Tevés in 2011 and is a one off Artist Proof signed by the artist, Sprayed in gold and then detailed on top. Frame not included

name: EXPLOSIVE MIND By Duster
description: Hand painted, decorated and sprayed onto thick card/board. We've had this one off piece by Duster hanging in the office for a while but now it's time to go to a good home. Painted in 2009 Duster has used a collection of Gold's, Silver's, Pink's and black to illustrate what he see's as the creative thinking of the human mind. A one off price for this one off piece due to the fact the corners are very slightly creased where it's been removed from the frame. You won't even notice when it's framed again. 590mm x 820mm Signed by the artist and dated 2009 Frame not included
